and really go all the way down through chapter 31

00:00:06.900 --> 00:00:10.939
in verse number 16 as we continue our journey

00:00:10.939 --> 00:00:12.420
through the book of Genesis

00:00:12.420 --> 00:00:15.000
and studying in this particular section of the book

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:16.700
through the life of Jacob.

00:00:16.700 --> 00:00:19.299
And of course, in our previous two studies

00:00:19.299 --> 00:00:20.459
through the book of Genesis,

00:00:20.459 --> 00:00:23.340
we have learned of the sons of Jacob

00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:27.459
as God has recorded for us 11 of those 12 sons

00:00:27.479 --> 00:00:31.040
that are born here, that are mentioned, of course,

00:00:31.040 --> 00:00:33.840
in chapter number, the end of chapter number 29

00:00:33.840 --> 00:00:35.599
and then in chapter number 30.

00:00:35.599 --> 00:00:37.900
Of course, Benjamin the 12th son

00:00:37.900 --> 00:00:41.360
is not recorded his birth until chapter number 35.

00:00:41.360 --> 00:00:42.880
We'll study the sons of Jacob

00:00:42.880 --> 00:00:44.840
and of course mentioned many things

00:00:44.840 --> 00:00:48.119
with regard to the events surrounding the birth

00:00:48.119 --> 00:00:51.560
of these 12, 11 sons that are mentioned here

00:00:51.560 --> 00:00:53.299
in this portion of scripture.

00:00:53.299 --> 00:00:55.919
And of course, I believe that we're able to learn

00:00:55.979 --> 00:00:57.939
valuable lessons of the importance

00:00:57.939 --> 00:00:59.860
of keeping our eyes on the Lord

00:00:59.860 --> 00:01:02.959
and walking with him and not allowing others

00:01:02.959 --> 00:01:05.480
to influence our walk with the Lord

00:01:05.480 --> 00:01:09.940
and to avoid, of course, as we looked at the carnality

00:01:09.940 --> 00:01:12.900
and the envy that was present

00:01:12.900 --> 00:01:16.059
within the relationships of Rachel and Leah

00:01:16.059 --> 00:01:17.940
and how we need to avoid those things

00:01:17.940 --> 00:01:21.099
and seek to honor the Lord with our lives.

00:01:21.099 --> 00:01:22.660
And so we studied that portion of scripture.

00:01:22.660 --> 00:01:25.180
Now, as we lead into the end of chapter number 30

00:01:25.239 --> 00:01:28.360
and really into the beginning of chapter number 31,

00:01:28.360 --> 00:01:31.639
we now find that the word of God is going to record for us

00:01:31.639 --> 00:01:34.819
some of the events or circumstances, if you will,

00:01:34.819 --> 00:01:38.720
that lead to Jacob's return to Canaan.

00:01:38.720 --> 00:01:42.879
You'll remember that at the end of the conversation

00:01:42.879 --> 00:01:47.279
between Jacob and his mom prior to leaving,

00:01:47.279 --> 00:01:51.440
remember Rebecca said, and Terry with him a few days

00:01:51.440 --> 00:01:53.720
in Genesis 27 and verse number 44,

00:01:53.720 --> 00:01:57.620
we've made note that those few days turned into years

00:01:57.620 --> 00:02:02.220
and was a situation in which she had never really expected

00:02:02.220 --> 00:02:04.059
that it would result in the way that it did.

00:02:04.059 --> 00:02:07.540
But now we find that these circumstances that are recorded

00:02:07.540 --> 00:02:10.020
are really going to lead back to that time

00:02:10.020 --> 00:02:13.139
in which Jacob would return to Canaan.

00:02:13.139 --> 00:02:16.300
In fact, in verse number 25, he makes that known.

00:02:16.300 --> 00:02:18.580
It says this in verse 25 of Genesis 30,

00:02:18.580 --> 00:02:22.139
and it came to pass when Rachel had born Joseph

00:02:22.139 --> 00:02:24.160
that Jacob said unto Laban,

00:02:24.160 --> 00:02:27.600
send me away that I may go unto mine own place

00:02:27.600 --> 00:02:29.039
and to my country.

00:02:29.039 --> 00:02:31.320
And we find that that request is made.

00:02:31.320 --> 00:02:33.860
I want you to notice verse number 43.

00:02:33.860 --> 00:02:36.639
The word of God says that the man increased exceedingly

00:02:36.639 --> 00:02:39.320
and had much cattle and maidservants and menservants

00:02:39.320 --> 00:02:41.360
and camels and asses.

00:02:41.360 --> 00:02:43.000
I've titled the message this evening

00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:45.240
really from verse number 43 there,

00:02:45.240 --> 00:02:48.399
that Jacob increased exceedingly.

00:02:48.399 --> 00:02:50.399
As we look at this passage of scripture again,

00:02:50.399 --> 00:02:51.740
we'll see some of the circumstances

00:02:51.740 --> 00:02:55.699
that are surrounding his eventual return to Canaan.

00:02:55.699 --> 00:02:58.619
We know that he's in this place for a purpose

00:02:58.619 --> 00:02:59.979
and for a time.

00:02:59.979 --> 00:03:03.619
In fact, we find that Jacob received that blessing

00:03:03.619 --> 00:03:06.320
from his father Isaac in Genesis chapter number 28

00:03:06.320 --> 00:03:09.699
with regard to leaving and going to Paddan Aram,

00:03:09.699 --> 00:03:12.059
and we find that that's exactly where he is.

00:03:12.059 --> 00:03:14.179
But notice as we look at this portion of scripture,

00:03:14.179 --> 00:03:15.580
if you're taking notes, first of all,

00:03:15.580 --> 00:03:17.600
his interaction with Laban.

00:03:17.600 --> 00:03:19.539
We find that this interaction is recorded

00:03:19.559 --> 00:03:20.720
in the portion of scripture.

00:03:20.720 --> 00:03:23.559
We've read about the, of course, marriage

00:03:23.559 --> 00:03:25.639
in chapter number 29 of Jacob,

00:03:25.639 --> 00:03:28.160
and then of course as the sons are born

00:03:28.160 --> 00:03:30.639
and all of that is provided to us.

00:03:30.639 --> 00:03:32.559
And now we find that the text of scripture

00:03:32.559 --> 00:03:35.279
focuses in on this interaction

00:03:35.279 --> 00:03:37.759
that Jacob is going to have with Laban.

00:03:37.759 --> 00:03:38.979
It begins with a request.

00:03:38.979 --> 00:03:40.919
I've read verse 25 already,

00:03:40.919 --> 00:03:43.059
and you find that at the end of verse number 25,

00:03:43.059 --> 00:03:44.240
the request is given.

00:03:44.240 --> 00:03:45.220
It's really straightforward.

00:03:45.220 --> 00:03:46.440
It's a plain request.

00:03:46.460 --> 00:03:48.500
He says, send me a way that I may go

00:03:48.500 --> 00:03:50.899
into my own place, into my country.

00:03:50.899 --> 00:03:53.100
He says, give me my wives and my children

00:03:53.100 --> 00:03:54.179
for whom I have served thee,

00:03:54.179 --> 00:03:57.259
and let me go for thou knowest my service,

00:03:57.259 --> 00:03:58.740
which I have done thee.

00:03:58.740 --> 00:04:00.179
And so the request is made.

00:04:00.179 --> 00:04:01.539
It's a simple request.

00:04:01.539 --> 00:04:03.919
We find that Laban responds,

00:04:03.919 --> 00:04:05.940
and in his responses, it's recorded to us

00:04:05.940 --> 00:04:07.460
in verse number 27.

00:04:07.460 --> 00:04:10.500
We really find that Laban recognizes

00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:13.539
the favor of God in the life of Jacob,

00:04:13.539 --> 00:04:16.339
and even how it's impacted Laban's own life.

00:04:17.200 --> 00:04:18.799
Notice what he says, and Laban said unto him,

00:04:18.799 --> 00:04:22.119
I pray thee, if I have found favor in thine eyes,

00:04:22.119 --> 00:04:24.000
tarry, and then notice what he says here

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:25.600
at the end of verse 27.

00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:27.559
For I have learned by experience

00:04:27.559 --> 00:04:31.059
that the Lord hath blessed me for thy sake.

00:04:31.059 --> 00:04:33.399
In fact, Jacob would reiterate this

00:04:33.399 --> 00:04:35.660
as he has this interaction.

00:04:35.660 --> 00:04:36.959
It says in verse 28, and he said,

00:04:36.959 --> 00:04:39.079
appoint me thy wages, and I will give it.

00:04:39.079 --> 00:04:41.799
And he said unto him, thou knowest how I have served thee,

00:04:41.799 --> 00:04:44.839
and how thy cattle was with me.

00:04:44.859 --> 00:04:47.899
For it was little which thou hadst before I came,

00:04:47.899 --> 00:04:50.980
and is now increased unto a multitude,

00:04:50.980 --> 00:04:55.059
and the Lord hath blessed thee since my coming.

00:04:55.059 --> 00:05:00.019
And now, when shall I provide for mine own house also?

00:05:00.019 --> 00:05:01.459
And so we find that this interaction

00:05:01.459 --> 00:05:03.779
begins with a request of departure.

00:05:03.779 --> 00:05:06.880
It is followed up by this recognition of the favor,

00:05:06.880 --> 00:05:09.420
the blessing of God that's been upon Jacob,

00:05:09.420 --> 00:05:11.579
but that also has impacted Laban,

00:05:11.579 --> 00:05:14.619
and he's recognized this blessing of God,

00:05:15.399 --> 00:05:17.200
and as we notice the interaction,

00:05:17.200 --> 00:05:19.160
we find that there's an agreement made

00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:20.739
in the text of scripture.

00:05:20.739 --> 00:05:23.600
Remember, there in verse number 28,

00:05:23.600 --> 00:05:26.359
that Laban said, appoint me thy wages, and I will give it.

00:05:26.359 --> 00:05:28.480
And we find that as you begin to look

00:05:28.480 --> 00:05:29.959
through the passage of scripture,

00:05:29.959 --> 00:05:32.079
that there's an agreement that is made.

00:05:32.079 --> 00:05:33.720
In verse 31 through 34,

00:05:33.720 --> 00:05:36.480
the terms of the agreement are laid out to us.

00:05:36.480 --> 00:05:38.480
It says, and he said, what shall I give thee?

00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:41.339
And Jacob said, thou shalt not give me anything.

00:05:41.339 --> 00:05:43.160
If thou wilt do this thing for me,

00:05:43.160 --> 00:05:46.059
I will again feed and keep thy flock.

00:05:46.059 --> 00:05:48.019
I will pass through all thy flock today,

00:05:48.019 --> 00:05:51.179
removing from thence all the speckled and spotted cattle,

00:05:51.179 --> 00:05:53.140
and all the brown cattle among the sheep,

00:05:53.140 --> 00:05:55.059
and the spotted and speckled among the goats,

00:05:55.059 --> 00:05:57.179
and of such shall be my hire.

00:05:57.179 --> 00:05:59.899
So shall my righteousness answer for me in time to come,

00:05:59.899 --> 00:06:02.739
when it shall come for my hire before thy face.

00:06:02.739 --> 00:06:05.660
Everyone that is not speckled and spotted among the goats,

00:06:05.660 --> 00:06:07.019
and brown among the sheep,

00:06:07.019 --> 00:06:09.619
that shall be counted stolen with me.

00:06:09.619 --> 00:06:11.459
Notice what the Bible says in verse 34,

00:06:11.459 --> 00:06:13.600
and Laban said, behold, I would,

00:06:13.600 --> 00:06:17.279
it might be according to thy word.

00:06:17.279 --> 00:06:18.519
There's an agreement that is made.

00:06:18.519 --> 00:06:20.359
The terms of the agreement are spelled out.

00:06:20.359 --> 00:06:22.040
We find that in the next several verses,

00:06:22.040 --> 00:06:25.179
the Bible talks about the removal of those cattle

00:06:25.179 --> 00:06:27.600
and the livestock, and we begin to read about

00:06:27.600 --> 00:06:30.559
the process of breeding in which Jacob employs,

00:06:30.559 --> 00:06:32.540
and all that takes place,

00:06:32.540 --> 00:06:35.339
and it tells us in verse 35, that he removed that day,

00:06:35.339 --> 00:06:38.200
that the he goats that were ring-streaked and spotted,

00:06:38.200 --> 00:06:40.399
and all the goats that were speckled and spotted,

00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:42.260
and everyone that had some white in it,

00:06:42.260 --> 00:06:43.380
and the brown among the sheep,

00:06:43.380 --> 00:06:45.700
and gave them into the hands of his sons.

00:06:45.700 --> 00:06:47.660
I'm not gonna continue to read all of the passage

00:06:47.660 --> 00:06:49.940
of scripture here, but we find that there's some practice

00:06:49.940 --> 00:06:53.119
that is used, that is employed by Jacob

00:06:53.119 --> 00:06:55.839
with regard to the selective breeding,

00:06:55.839 --> 00:06:59.899
and we see that he obviously had some knowledge from God

00:06:59.899 --> 00:07:01.660
with regard to those things,

00:07:01.660 --> 00:07:04.339
but I want you to understand that as we look at

00:07:04.339 --> 00:07:07.040
all of that process, that it really leads us

00:07:07.040 --> 00:07:09.100
to our second thought this evening,

00:07:09.119 --> 00:07:11.279
and that's not just the interaction with Laban,

00:07:11.279 --> 00:07:13.600
but it's the increase from God,

00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:15.019
the increase from the Lord.

00:07:15.019 --> 00:07:18.760
We find that here as we get to verse number 43,

00:07:18.760 --> 00:07:21.880
the Bible says, and the man increased exceedingly,

00:07:21.880 --> 00:07:24.380
and had much cattle, and made servants,

00:07:24.380 --> 00:07:27.959
and men servants, and camels, and asses,

00:07:27.959 --> 00:07:30.200
and I want you to see where the scriptures tell us

00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:32.799
that his increase is from the Lord.

00:07:32.799 --> 00:07:34.440
In fact, in chapter number 31,

00:07:34.440 --> 00:07:37.000
if you look down at verse number nine,

00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:40.500
in this particular verse, we find that Jacob here

00:07:40.500 --> 00:07:43.700
is speaking to Rachel and Leah, and he says this,

00:07:43.700 --> 00:07:47.140
thus God hath taken away the cattle of your father,

00:07:47.140 --> 00:07:50.980
and given them to me, and he's speaking specifically

00:07:50.980 --> 00:07:52.980
about all of that breeding process,

00:07:52.980 --> 00:07:56.200
and all that was taking place in verse 36,

00:07:56.200 --> 00:07:57.980
down through verse number 42,

00:07:57.980 --> 00:08:00.260
and as we think about the increase from the Lord,

00:08:00.260 --> 00:08:03.299
we find really that this is fulfilled promise.

00:08:03.299 --> 00:08:04.940
Go back, if you will, hold your place here,

00:08:04.940 --> 00:08:06.619
and go back to chapter 28.

00:08:06.619 --> 00:08:08.000
One thing that we can rejoice in

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:09.359
as we look at the word of God,

00:08:09.359 --> 00:08:10.640
and as we study the scriptures,

00:08:10.640 --> 00:08:13.160
and begin to examine the lives of those

00:08:13.160 --> 00:08:14.399
that have gone before us,

00:08:14.399 --> 00:08:16.600
and as we begin to think about our own lives,

00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:20.160
is that we have a book that God has given us

00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:22.480
that is full of promises.

00:08:22.480 --> 00:08:24.480
When we think about the promises of God,

00:08:24.480 --> 00:08:27.160
and we understand that Peter says this,

00:08:27.160 --> 00:08:29.799
that they're exceeding great and precious promises,

00:08:29.799 --> 00:08:33.400
and we sing songs such as Standing on the Promises,

00:08:33.400 --> 00:08:36.059
and we think about the promises of God,

00:08:36.440 --> 00:08:38.559
and the reality this evening is that we ought

00:08:38.559 --> 00:08:40.919
to rejoice greatly for every promise

00:08:40.919 --> 00:08:42.520
that God has given us.

00:08:42.520 --> 00:08:44.760
In fact, we find that the Bible says this

00:08:44.760 --> 00:08:46.960
