00:08:46.960 --> 00:08:51.000
for all the promises of God in him are yea,

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:56.000
and in him, amen, unto the glory of God by us.

00:08:56.799 --> 00:08:59.039
God's made some promises.

00:08:59.039 --> 00:09:02.200
Here, as we think about the life of Jacob in particular,

00:09:02.200 --> 00:09:05.039
and we see back in the 28th chapter,

00:09:05.039 --> 00:09:07.380
as he would depart from his home,

00:09:07.380 --> 00:09:10.799
not knowing all that would befall him,

00:09:10.799 --> 00:09:12.739
it's Isaac that speaks to him.

00:09:12.739 --> 00:09:14.859
Notice in verse number one,

00:09:14.859 --> 00:09:16.659
the Bible says that Isaac called Jacob,

00:09:16.659 --> 00:09:19.020
and blessed him, and charged him,

00:09:19.020 --> 00:09:20.039
and said unto him,

00:09:20.039 --> 00:09:23.460
thou shalt not take a wife of the daughters of Canaan.

00:09:23.460 --> 00:09:25.260
Arise, go to Paddan Aram,

00:09:25.260 --> 00:09:28.419
and to the house of Bethuel, thy mother's father,

00:09:28.419 --> 00:09:30.539
and take thee a wife from thence

00:09:30.539 --> 00:09:33.820
of the daughters of Laban, thy mother's brother.

00:09:33.840 --> 00:09:35.880
And notice what he says in verses three and four.

00:09:35.880 --> 00:09:38.599
And God Almighty bless thee,

00:09:38.599 --> 00:09:41.559
and make thee fruitful, and multiply thee,

00:09:41.559 --> 00:09:44.840
that thou mayest be a multitude of people,

00:09:44.840 --> 00:09:47.640
and give thee the blessing of Abraham to thee,

00:09:47.640 --> 00:09:49.280
and to thy seed with thee,

00:09:49.280 --> 00:09:52.159
and that thou mayest inherit the land whereon thou art

00:09:52.159 --> 00:09:56.080
a stranger which God gave unto Abraham.

00:09:56.080 --> 00:09:58.799
And at that moment, after those words,

00:09:58.799 --> 00:10:00.320
the Bible says that Isaac,

00:10:00.320 --> 00:10:04.520
sent away Jacob, in verse number five.

00:10:04.520 --> 00:10:06.120
And as Jacob was sent away,

00:10:06.120 --> 00:10:08.480
it picks up and tells us in verse number 10

00:10:08.480 --> 00:10:12.840
that Jacob went out from Beersheba and went toward Haran.

00:10:12.840 --> 00:10:15.640
We've mentioned already in previous studies

00:10:15.640 --> 00:10:18.960
that Paddan Aram is the chief city of Haran,

00:10:18.960 --> 00:10:20.340
and he's going to the place

00:10:20.340 --> 00:10:22.520
where he's been instructed to do so.

00:10:22.520 --> 00:10:23.960
And it's during that journey

00:10:23.960 --> 00:10:26.740
that he has that dream, that vision.

00:10:26.740 --> 00:10:28.380
And notice as you pick it up with me

00:10:28.380 --> 00:10:30.800
in verse number 13 of Genesis 28,

00:10:30.800 --> 00:10:32.560
the Bible says that behold,

00:10:32.560 --> 00:10:36.080
the Lord stood above it and said.

00:10:36.080 --> 00:10:38.540
As you read verses 13 through 15,

00:10:38.540 --> 00:10:40.440
I would say that you could summarize

00:10:40.440 --> 00:10:42.360
these three verses of Scripture

00:10:42.360 --> 00:10:46.180
by saying God has given Jacob some encouraging promises.

00:10:46.180 --> 00:10:48.720
God is speaking directly to Jacob

00:10:48.720 --> 00:10:52.160
and He's giving him some very specific promises.

00:10:52.160 --> 00:10:56.240
It says, I am the Lord God of Abraham, thy father,

00:10:56.300 --> 00:10:59.820
and the God of Isaac, the land whereon thou liest.

00:10:59.820 --> 00:11:03.460
To thee will I give it and to thy seed.

00:11:03.460 --> 00:11:05.620
Thy seed shall be as the dust of the earth

00:11:05.620 --> 00:11:08.060
and thou shalt spread abroad to the west

00:11:08.060 --> 00:11:11.200
and to the east and to the north and to the south.

00:11:11.200 --> 00:11:12.820
And in thee and in thy seed

00:11:12.820 --> 00:11:17.580
shall all the families of the earth be blessed.

00:11:17.580 --> 00:11:21.140
Notice, it's interesting because God is giving this promise

00:11:21.140 --> 00:11:23.420
and He says the land whereon thou liest

00:11:23.420 --> 00:11:26.180
in verse number 13, to thee will I give it

00:11:26.180 --> 00:11:29.840
and to thy seed, but He's leaving that land, right?

00:11:29.840 --> 00:11:32.400
He's departing from that place

00:11:32.400 --> 00:11:35.040
because He's fleeing because of the circumstances

00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:39.040
of the stolen blessing and all that took place.

00:11:39.040 --> 00:11:41.640
And we find that God then says in verse number 15,

00:11:41.640 --> 00:11:44.240
and behold, I am with thee

00:11:45.880 --> 00:11:50.880
and will keep thee in all places whither thou goest

00:11:51.760 --> 00:11:55.780
and will bring thee again into this land.

00:11:55.800 --> 00:11:58.880
For I will not leave thee until I have done that

00:11:58.880 --> 00:12:02.580
which I have spoken to thee of.

00:12:02.580 --> 00:12:05.200
Now, those are some encouraging promises.

00:12:05.200 --> 00:12:06.520
Begin to think about Jacob.

00:12:06.520 --> 00:12:09.400
Of course, we know as we studied the 28th chapter

00:12:09.400 --> 00:12:12.400
and I won't rehash everything that I've recently said

00:12:12.400 --> 00:12:14.680
just a few weeks ago in Genesis chapter 28,

