00:12:18.400 --> 00:12:19.640
His life was changed.

00:12:19.640 --> 00:12:22.200
We've likened this passage of Scripture

00:12:22.200 --> 00:12:24.960
to when we were saved, when we were converted.

00:12:24.980 --> 00:12:29.060
And you think about the promises that God gives to Jacob

00:12:29.060 --> 00:12:30.260
in this portion of Scripture.

00:12:30.260 --> 00:12:32.780
And then as we come to Genesis chapter number 30,

00:12:32.780 --> 00:12:36.700
and we find that the passage ends in verse number 43

00:12:36.700 --> 00:12:39.540
by speaking about the increase.

00:12:39.540 --> 00:12:42.620
This man, it says, and the man increased exceedingly

00:12:42.620 --> 00:12:45.600
and had much cattle and maidservants and menservants

00:12:45.600 --> 00:12:47.380
and camels and asses.

00:12:47.380 --> 00:12:49.780
And remember the Bible said there

00:12:49.780 --> 00:12:52.700
that God was going to be with him.

00:12:52.700 --> 00:12:54.660
He was gonna keep him in all places

00:12:55.520 --> 00:12:58.000
and bring thee again into this land

00:12:58.000 --> 00:12:59.240
for I will not leave thee.

00:12:59.240 --> 00:13:01.880
Notice what he says, until I have done that

00:13:01.880 --> 00:13:04.600
which I have spoken to thee of.

00:13:04.600 --> 00:13:07.880
God was working and God was doing.

00:13:07.880 --> 00:13:11.480
And we find that God is fulfilling his promises.

00:13:11.480 --> 00:13:12.300
Can I say this?

00:13:12.300 --> 00:13:14.540
God always fulfills his promises.

00:13:15.760 --> 00:13:18.000
You have promises that you hold dear

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:20.640
as we sing the song standing on his promises,

00:13:20.640 --> 00:13:23.600
as we take testimonies and we sing about

00:13:23.620 --> 00:13:26.420
and testify about the promises of God,

00:13:26.420 --> 00:13:29.100
we hold dear to those promises.

00:13:29.100 --> 00:13:32.220
And we understand that God is faithful

00:13:32.220 --> 00:13:35.180
and that God will honor his word.

00:13:36.500 --> 00:13:39.380
I'm so thankful as we look at the word of God

00:13:39.380 --> 00:13:40.720
and consider the promises.

00:13:40.720 --> 00:13:42.140
Of course, there are some promises

00:13:42.140 --> 00:13:43.800
that we look to in the word of God

00:13:43.800 --> 00:13:45.900
that are promises that we would categorize

00:13:45.900 --> 00:13:48.260
as being conditional promises.

00:13:48.260 --> 00:13:50.500
Often when we speak about conditional promises,

00:13:50.500 --> 00:13:53.720
we speak of promises that are oftentimes

00:13:53.720 --> 00:13:58.080
the most common way that these promises are referred to

00:13:58.080 --> 00:14:00.360
as if-then promise.

00:14:00.360 --> 00:14:04.200
If you do this, then God promises to do this.

00:14:04.200 --> 00:14:05.900
And when you think about those promises

00:14:05.900 --> 00:14:10.080
and you consider that God has given us his very word,

00:14:10.080 --> 00:14:11.800
if you do these things,

00:14:11.800 --> 00:14:14.360
that God promises that he will do this.

00:14:14.360 --> 00:14:15.720
And I'm thankful for that

00:14:15.720 --> 00:14:18.480
because God has given us the instruction

00:14:18.500 --> 00:14:20.640
with regard to these promises.

00:14:20.640 --> 00:14:22.740
In fact, as you read Proverbs chapter number two,

00:14:22.740 --> 00:14:23.940
there's a whole list of them

00:14:23.940 --> 00:14:28.619
in that very passage of scripture of if-then promises.

00:14:28.619 --> 00:14:30.140
But then as we come to the word of God,

00:14:30.140 --> 00:14:32.140
we find that not only do we come across

00:14:32.140 --> 00:14:33.740
conditional promises,

00:14:33.740 --> 00:14:35.100
but we find that the word of God

00:14:35.100 --> 00:14:38.020
contains unconditional promises.

00:14:38.020 --> 00:14:41.260
Promises that God has made that have no impact

00:14:41.260 --> 00:14:45.300
on what we do or do not do with regard to those promises.

00:14:45.300 --> 00:14:48.300
Can I tell you that we sang about one of those this evening?

00:14:48.320 --> 00:14:49.960
Coming again, right?

00:14:49.960 --> 00:14:51.800
Did not Jesus give us a promise

00:14:51.800 --> 00:14:53.480
that he was going to return?

00:14:53.480 --> 00:14:57.559
That promise stands as an unconditional promise.

00:14:57.559 --> 00:15:00.000
God himself has promised.

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:02.399
He said, let not your hearts be troubled.

00:15:02.399 --> 00:15:04.480
You believe in God, believe also in me.

00:15:04.480 --> 00:15:06.320
In my father's house are many mansions.

00:15:06.320 --> 00:15:07.760
If it were not so, I would have told you.

00:15:07.760 --> 00:15:09.960
I go to prepare a place for you.

00:15:09.960 --> 00:15:12.320
And he said this, if I go and prepare a place for you,

00:15:12.320 --> 00:15:17.279
I will come again and receive you unto myself

00:15:17.300 --> 00:15:20.779
that where I am, there ye may be also.

00:15:20.779 --> 00:15:23.220
We find that the word of God says that Jesus,

00:15:23.220 --> 00:15:24.980
as we would think about the truth

00:15:24.980 --> 00:15:26.460
of the promise of his return,

00:15:26.460 --> 00:15:29.260
that there are some, according to 2 Peter 3,

00:15:29.260 --> 00:15:30.940
that mock that very promise

00:15:30.940 --> 00:15:32.540
that we're speaking of this evening.

00:15:32.540 --> 00:15:35.339
And they say, where is the promise of his return?

00:15:37.580 --> 00:15:38.940
And Peter responds and says,

00:15:38.940 --> 00:15:43.940
the Lord is not slack concerning his promise.

00:15:45.140 --> 00:15:46.760
As some men count slackness.

00:15:47.179 --> 00:15:49.220
But his long-suffering to us word,

00:15:49.220 --> 00:15:51.500
not willing that any should perish,

00:15:51.500 --> 00:15:54.140
but that all should come to repentance.

00:15:54.140 --> 00:15:57.899
Listen, God is not slack concerning any of his promises.

00:15:57.899 --> 00:16:01.339
What he hath promised, he will do.

00:16:01.339 --> 00:16:02.660
And we ought to rejoice in that.

00:16:02.660 --> 00:16:03.980
You know, he told us that his word

00:16:03.980 --> 00:16:05.540
will not return unto him void,

00:16:05.540 --> 00:16:08.059
that it will accomplish what he has set forth

00:16:08.059 --> 00:16:09.100
for it to accomplish.

00:16:09.100 --> 00:16:10.940
He's told us that we're to preach the word,

00:16:10.940 --> 00:16:12.580
to be instant in season, out of season,

00:16:12.580 --> 00:16:14.059
reprove, rebuke, exhort,

00:16:14.059 --> 00:16:15.580
with all long-suffering and doctrine.

00:16:15.580 --> 00:16:16.420
Why?

00:16:16.420 --> 00:16:18.839
Because God's promised to use his word.

00:16:19.880 --> 00:16:21.640
And as we take God at his word,

00:16:21.640 --> 00:16:24.720
and we take the promises that he's given us,

00:16:24.720 --> 00:16:26.200
and we claim those promises,

00:16:26.200 --> 00:16:27.880
we can rejoice this evening

00:16:27.880 --> 00:16:30.480
that as we look at the increase from the Lord,

00:16:30.480 --> 00:16:33.520
as we look at what's taken place in the life of Jacob

00:16:33.520 --> 00:16:36.720
over these years that he spent in this land,

00:16:36.720 --> 00:16:39.960
and we see how God has fulfilled these promises

00:16:39.960 --> 00:16:41.420
that he's made to Jacob.

00:16:42.520 --> 00:16:44.720
As we evaluate our lives,

00:16:44.720 --> 00:16:46.540
is it not true that we can see

00:16:46.540 --> 00:16:48.740
how God has been faithful to the promises

00:16:48.740 --> 00:16:49.860
that he's given us?

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:52.300
I'm thankful for that promise,

00:16:52.300 --> 00:16:55.059
and often as we take testimony specifically

00:16:55.059 --> 00:16:57.660
with regard to promises from his word,

00:16:57.660 --> 00:16:59.899
we think of the promise of his presence.

00:17:01.100 --> 00:17:04.820
We often quote Hebrews 13 in verse number five,

00:17:04.820 --> 00:17:08.619
that portion of that verse of Scripture that says,

00:17:08.619 --> 00:17:11.660
I will never leave thee nor forsake thee.

00:17:11.660 --> 00:17:13.300
Isn't that precious?

00:17:13.320 --> 00:17:14.960
We find that even in this text

00:17:14.960 --> 00:17:17.600
that Jacob speaks about that very thing.

00:17:17.600 --> 00:17:19.839
As we think about the increase from the Lord,

00:17:19.839 --> 00:17:21.960
we find that there are fulfilled promises.

00:17:21.960 --> 00:17:24.800
It tells us of much cattle, of maidservants,

00:17:24.800 --> 00:17:27.600
of menservants, of camels and asses,

00:17:27.600 --> 00:17:31.200
but we find that due to this increase from the Lord,

00:17:31.200 --> 00:17:32.880
due to these fulfilled promises,

00:17:32.880 --> 00:17:36.399
that we find that there's hostility that he faces.

00:17:37.440 --> 00:17:39.080
And we find that here,

00:17:39.080 --> 00:17:42.320
as we continue and move into the 31st chapter,

00:17:42.339 --> 00:17:46.580
the Bible says that he heard the words of Laban's sons.

00:17:46.580 --> 00:17:50.020
Notice what these sons of Laban are saying.

00:17:50.020 --> 00:17:53.860
Jacob hath taken away all that was our father's,

00:17:53.860 --> 00:17:55.820
and of that which was our father's,

00:17:55.820 --> 00:17:59.020
hath he begotten all this glory.

00:17:59.020 --> 00:18:01.540
And Jacob beheld the countenance of Laban,

00:18:02.460 --> 00:18:06.300
and behold, it was not toward him as before.

00:18:06.300 --> 00:18:09.899
We find that there's this open hostility, if you will,

00:18:09.899 --> 00:18:12.920
we begin to see how Jacob is going to speak

00:18:12.920 --> 00:18:16.440
with Rachel and Leah with regard to his plan,

00:18:16.440 --> 00:18:19.160
and really it goes back to where we started this evening

00:18:19.160 --> 00:18:21.440
in verse number 25, when he says to Laban,

00:18:21.440 --> 00:18:24.600
send me away, that I may go into mine own place,

00:18:24.600 --> 00:18:25.480
into my own country.

00:18:25.480 --> 00:18:28.160
He asks the question at the end of verse number 30,

00:18:28.160 --> 00:18:31.800
when shall I provide for my own house also?

00:18:32.760 --> 00:18:35.200
We find that as he would have this increase,

00:18:35.200 --> 00:18:37.799
as he would experience this blessing of the Lord,

00:18:37.820 --> 00:18:40.020
that there comes some opposition, if you will,

00:18:40.020 --> 00:18:42.979
there's some hostility that he faces.

00:18:42.979 --> 00:18:45.260
You know, the reality is that the enemy

00:18:45.260 --> 00:18:48.020
is always seeking to oppose the child of God.

00:18:48.900 --> 00:18:51.960
The enemy is always seeking to oppose the child of God.

00:18:51.960 --> 00:18:53.380
You read through the scriptures,

00:18:53.380 --> 00:18:56.220
and you read of the men and women of God

00:18:56.220 --> 00:18:59.100
who sought to do something for the Lord,

00:18:59.100 --> 00:19:01.500
for the cause of exalting and magnifying

00:19:01.500 --> 00:19:05.080
the name of the Lord, there's opposition that they face.

00:19:05.080 --> 00:19:06.940
You think about the Apostle Paul when he speaks

00:19:06.960 --> 00:19:10.119
about the open door that God has given,

00:19:10.119 --> 00:19:14.239
but he says there are many adversaries.

00:19:14.239 --> 00:19:17.080
And we face opposition in this life,

00:19:17.080 --> 00:19:19.760
but we must understand and we must realize

00:19:19.760 --> 00:19:22.960
that it's important for us to fix our attention

00:19:22.960 --> 00:19:24.179
upon our Lord.

00:19:25.600 --> 00:19:29.720
See, if we put too much of our focus upon the opposition,

00:19:29.720 --> 00:19:32.380
if we put too much of our attention and our focus

00:19:32.380 --> 00:19:35.660
upon the adversary, then we become overwhelmed.

00:19:36.640 --> 00:19:38.520
We can become defeated.

00:19:38.520 --> 00:19:40.640
We understand that our enemy wants to,

00:19:40.640 --> 00:19:44.400
not only discourage us, our enemy wants to destroy us.

00:19:45.520 --> 00:19:48.359
And there are times in which he will use adversity.

00:19:48.359 --> 00:19:50.280
There are times in which he will use

00:19:50.280 --> 00:19:54.359
the opposition of others to devour us.

00:19:55.559 --> 00:19:58.640
We find here this evening that after Jacob

00:19:58.640 --> 00:20:00.359
is aware of this hostility.

00:20:00.359 --> 00:20:02.799
and after he hears the words,

00:20:02.799 --> 00:20:05.239
and after he sees the countenance

00:20:05.239 --> 00:20:07.439
in verse one and two of chapter 31,

00:20:07.439 --> 00:20:10.039
I want you to see something just wonderful

00:20:10.039 --> 00:20:12.359
because the Bible, the very next verse that we see,

00:20:12.359 --> 00:20:15.999
the Bible says, and the Lord said unto Jacob.

00:20:15.999 --> 00:20:19.039
I am thankful that when you hear the words

00:20:19.039 --> 00:20:22.339
of the opposition, when you see the countenance

00:20:22.339 --> 00:20:25.639
of the opposition, when you begin to face the hostility

00:20:25.639 --> 00:20:28.879
that Jacob was going to encounter and endure,

00:20:28.879 --> 00:20:31.019
that God speaks to his man.

00:20:32.759 --> 00:20:34.359
You know, God uses his word.

00:20:35.679 --> 00:20:39.779
Jacob did not have what we have in our hands this evening.

00:20:40.779 --> 00:20:42.959
Genesis had not even been written yet,

00:20:42.959 --> 00:20:47.319
for Moses was not yet on the scene, amen?

00:20:47.319 --> 00:20:49.239
And the reality is that we have

00:20:49.239 --> 00:20:51.919
the complete canon of Scripture,

00:20:51.919 --> 00:20:54.319
and we go to this book and we begin

00:20:54.319 --> 00:20:56.399
to open the pages of this book,

00:20:56.399 --> 00:20:59.479
and guess what, God speaks to us.

00:20:59.479 --> 00:21:02.479
He begins to reveal to us promises

00:21:02.479 --> 00:21:04.159
and to remind us of promises,

00:21:04.159 --> 00:21:06.279
and he gives us direction for our lives,

00:21:06.279 --> 00:21:08.319
and when we face the opposition,

00:21:08.319 --> 00:21:10.279
when we deal with the adversity,

00:21:10.279 --> 00:21:12.579
oh, what a lesson for us to learn this evening

00:21:12.579 --> 00:21:15.199
how we must run to this book,

00:21:15.199 --> 00:21:17.719
and we must listen for the voice of God.

00:21:19.359 --> 00:21:22.939
I've heard people say, God's just not speaking to me.

00:21:22.939 --> 00:21:24.779
How much are we reading of his word?

00:21:25.779 --> 00:21:27.659
Often, I found in my own life,

00:21:27.659 --> 00:21:30.419
and I found in those lives of those

00:21:30.419 --> 00:21:32.899
that have testified and I've interacted with,

00:21:32.899 --> 00:21:36.159
that oftentimes, the problem isn't with God speaking.

00:21:37.359 --> 00:21:39.819
The problem is with us as his servants hearing.

00:21:40.779 --> 00:21:41.619
Amen?

00:21:42.939 --> 00:21:46.259
Oftentimes, we're not hearing what God is saying.

00:21:46.259 --> 00:21:49.819
We're not listening for that still, small voice.

00:21:49.819 --> 00:21:52.659
We're not following the admonition

00:21:52.659 --> 00:21:54.499
of the psalmist to be still

00:21:55.539 --> 00:21:58.099
and to know that he is God.

00:21:58.099 --> 00:22:00.259
And this evening, we find that in the midst

00:22:00.259 --> 00:22:01.839
of all that was taking place

00:22:01.839 --> 00:22:05.259
and all that was transpiring in the life of Jacob,

00:22:05.259 --> 00:22:08.499
that the Lord speaks to Jacob.

00:22:08.499 --> 00:22:10.699
How precious that is.

00:22:10.699 --> 00:22:14.499
And it leads us to our third thought this evening,

00:22:14.499 --> 00:22:16.619
the instruction from the Lord.

00:22:16.619 --> 00:22:18.979
I would simply say that the instruction

00:22:18.979 --> 00:22:20.499
is given in verse number three,

00:22:20.499 --> 00:22:22.699
and it's simple instruction,

00:22:22.699 --> 00:22:24.499
and it really follows with regard

00:22:24.499 --> 00:22:26.939
to the desire that he's already expressed

00:22:26.939 --> 00:22:29.379
as he spoke with Laban in verse 25.

00:22:29.379 --> 00:22:30.899
And now here in verse number three,

00:22:30.899 --> 00:22:32.499
notice the word of God.

00:22:32.499 --> 00:22:35.439
It says, the Lord said unto Jacob,

00:22:35.439 --> 00:22:38.339
return unto the land of thy fathers

00:22:38.339 --> 00:22:39.979
and to thy kindred,

00:22:39.979 --> 00:22:41.739
and I will be with thee.

00:22:41.739 --> 00:22:43.219
Return.

00:22:43.219 --> 00:22:45.139
The divine direction is given.

00:22:46.059 --> 00:22:47.019
And it's interesting to me

00:22:47.019 --> 00:22:49.199
that in the next several verses of Scripture,

00:22:49.199 --> 00:22:50.939
really from verse four all the way down

00:22:50.939 --> 00:22:52.519
to verse number 13,

00:22:52.519 --> 00:22:55.959
that Jacob is now speaking to Rachel and Leah.

00:22:55.959 --> 00:22:58.399
As Jacob is rehearsing the instruction

00:22:58.399 --> 00:23:00.159
that he's received from the Lord,

00:23:00.159 --> 00:23:01.839
we find that as we dig in

00:23:01.839 --> 00:23:05.959
and we begin to examine that which Jacob

00:23:05.959 --> 00:23:08.139
is communicating to Rachel and Leah

00:23:08.139 --> 00:23:11.239
within the context of this conversation,

00:23:11.239 --> 00:23:14.739
we find that we are reminded of some precious truth,

00:23:14.739 --> 00:23:18.199
and really Jacob is reminding not only himself,

00:23:18.199 --> 00:23:20.759
but he's reminding Rachel and Leah of this truth.

00:23:21.839 --> 00:23:24.079
Notice as it begins in verse number four,

00:23:24.079 --> 00:23:26.599
and Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah

00:23:26.599 --> 00:23:29.079
to the field unto his flock and said unto them.

00:23:29.079 --> 00:23:31.559
So again, as we look at these next verses

00:23:31.559 --> 00:23:34.719
from verse number five here down through verse number 13,

00:23:34.719 --> 00:23:35.959
Jacob is rehearsing.

00:23:35.959 --> 00:23:39.879
He's given the information to Rachel and Leah

00:23:39.879 --> 00:23:41.079
that he has received,

00:23:41.079 --> 00:23:42.439
and notice what he says.

00:23:42.439 --> 00:23:43.959
I see your father's countenance

00:23:43.959 --> 00:23:46.759
that is not toward me as before.

00:23:46.759 --> 00:23:48.879
Notice this first thing that he says,

00:23:48.879 --> 00:23:52.799
but the God of my father hath been with me.

00:23:52.799 --> 00:23:56.119
But the God of my father hath been with me.

00:23:56.119 --> 00:23:57.639
We find that as we think about

00:23:57.639 --> 00:24:00.519
the instruction that God has given,

00:24:00.519 --> 00:24:03.779
and as we think about the way in which Jacob

00:24:03.779 --> 00:24:06.559
is now communicating these things to Rachel and Leah,

00:24:06.559 --> 00:24:08.979
we've already seen the plan of God.

00:24:08.979 --> 00:24:10.799
Now we're seeing the presence of God.

00:24:10.799 --> 00:24:12.779
We find that he testifies,

00:24:12.779 --> 00:24:16.819
but the God of my father hath been with me.

00:24:16.819 --> 00:24:18.859
Listen, there might be some folks that oppose us.

00:24:18.859 --> 00:24:20.579
He says in the very text,

00:24:20.579 --> 00:24:22.179
I see your father's countenance

00:24:22.179 --> 00:24:24.859
that it's not toward me as before,

00:24:24.859 --> 00:24:26.739
but God's been with me.

00:24:26.739 --> 00:24:28.139
God's been with me.

00:24:28.139 --> 00:24:30.639
Is that not what God promised?

00:24:30.639 --> 00:24:32.619
Remember back in chapter 28,

00:24:32.619 --> 00:24:35.539
I don't want to just belabor the point,

00:24:35.539 --> 00:24:39.659
but notice in chapter 28 that God said in verse number 15,

00:24:39.739 --> 00:24:41.659
behold, I am with thee.

00:24:44.859 --> 00:24:48.439
What a precious promise of the Word of God.

00:24:48.439 --> 00:24:51.219
We rejoice when we read of those

00:24:51.219 --> 00:24:52.339
that have gone before us

00:24:52.339 --> 00:24:54.139
that have received this same promise.

00:24:54.139 --> 00:24:55.099
Think about this.

00:24:55.099 --> 00:24:56.459
Turn to the book of Joshua, if you will,

00:24:56.459 --> 00:24:57.739
in the first chapter,

00:24:57.739 --> 00:25:01.739
and I want you to see how God encourages Joshua.

